I say this after watching every Magical Journey but this time you guys truly outdid yourself, this is absolutely magical, stunning. This video, the set, choreography, cinematography, is not only unprecedented for Coke Studio in Pakistan but anywhere else in the world. I can't remember watching anything like this. The part about the Gharvi group gave me chills. Imagine a neighbourhood like that existing anywhere in the world. A truly unique place. 
You're all magicians, not just among the best in Pakistan but the world.  May Allah bless you for bringing out Pakistani stories and narratives that have been ignored for so long.

snippet.textDisplay:
Great effort by every one, set designers, quick style, behind the scene teams, dancers.  There are very few singers with a swag like Faris. Butt and the female singers did a great job. Brilliant concept! Loved all the transitions in the actual video. 
My only issue with this song is the sound quality or mixing! Humungous effort behind  this song, yet the sound and beats were so typical and generic! The lyrics were fun as well (esp female part), but, repetitive use of words like 'love meray nuch le' and 'way marjania'.. made certain parts of the song a bit flat
